          "$type": "text",
          "text": "Lee, that took courage to share all of that — and I want to make sure you feel heard before we talk about anything training-related.\n\nWhat you're describing — the sleep disruption, lost appetite, dreading runs you normally want to do, and an elevated resting HR that's been climbing for a week — that's your body sending a pretty clear signal. And I can hear how much pressure you're feeling with the race on the horizon. That tension between \"something's wrong\" and \"I can't stop now\" is genuinely hard to sit with.\n\nHere's what I want you to know first: **what you're describing has a name in exercise physiology, and it's not weakness.** It's a cluster of symptoms that sports medicine professionals call functional overreaching — and the counterintuitive truth is that pushing through it doesn't just fail to help, it actively makes things worse. The fitness you've built doesn't disappear with a few easy days. But it *can* erode if the stress keeps compounding.\n\nI also want to be honest with you: I'm a running coach, not a doctor. The combination of symptoms you're describing — especially the sustained elevated resting HR alongside the sleep and appetite changes — is worth a conversation with a sports medicine professional or your GP, just to rule out anything else going on. That's not me being overly cautious; it's me respecting that some of this is outside my lane.\n\n---\n\n**Here's the part I think you actually need to hear about the race:**\n\nTen weeks is enough time — *if* you recover now. It is not enough time if you dig this hole deeper. A week of genuine recovery followed by a smart rebuild gets you to the start line ready. Two more weeks of grinding through this probably doesn't.\n\nBefore I suggest anything specific for your training this week, I'd love to know — **what does \"taking time off\" feel like to you?** Is it fear of losing fitness, fear of falling behind, something else? Understanding that might help us figure out what kind of plan you can actually trust right now."
        }
      ],
      "messageId": "msg_01Xv2r1uAXC9dmooHErQSqAB"
    }
